item.title: Rachael add a quote by D.H. Lawrence
item.description: "But that is how men are! Ungrateful and never satisfied. When you don't have them they hate you because you won't; and when you do have them they hate you again, for some other reason. Or for no reason at all, except that they are discontented children, and can't be satisfied whatever they get, let a woman do what she may." -- D.H. Lawrence

item.title: Rachael add a quote by George Orwell
item.description: "It's a beautiful thing, the destruction of words." -- George Orwell

item.title: Rachael add a quote by Ramona Quimby as written by Beverly Cleary
item.description: "If she can't spell, why is she a librarian? Librarians should know how to spell." -- Ramona Quimby as written by Beverly Cleary

item.title: Rachael add a quote by Hunter S. Thompson
item.description: "I felt a little guilty about jangling the poor bugger's brains with that evil fantasy. But what the hell? Anybody who wanders around the world saying, "Hell yes, I'm from Texas," deserves whatever happens to him." -- Hunter S. Thompson

item.title: Rachael add a quote by Victor Hugo
item.description: "To love another person is to see the face of God." -- Victor Hugo
